This paper deals with the problem of estimating a sparse inverse covariance matrix, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes a novel algorithm for solving the resulting optimization problem, which is a regularized log-determinant program. This problem is closely related to topics in several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), scientific computing (cs.SI), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
